<HEADLINE>
<P>
FLAG BURNING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I've read the articles and letters to the editor regarding the Supreme Court's 
flag-burning decision and the hoopla about a possible constitutional amendment. 
Give us all a break! There's a very easy way to stop all this nonsense and 
satisfy the pro- and anti-burners using laws that probably already are on the 
books. 
</P>
<P>
If someone burns a flag he's arrested for either burning without a permit or 
polluting the air. In this way you can burn all the flags you want but you have 
to do it where there are no anti-open fire ordinances or no clean air 
regulations. Simple, everybody's satisfied. 
</P>
<P>
MICHAEL STRATTON 
</P>
<P>
Brea 
</P>
</TEXT>
