<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY ALLOTTED AN OFFICIAL 3RD WORD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Is the community above Hansen Dam known as Lakeview Terrace or Lake View 
Terrace? 
</P>
<P>
The Los Angeles City Council ended the confusion Tuesday. The name, which often 
appears on city reports and correspondence, is now officially Lake View Terrace 
-- that's three words, all beginning with capital letters. 
</P>
<P>
Councilman Ernani Bernardi, who represents the community, said in a motion that 
city records and maps show that the community is three words, not two, and 
ordered that all further references be accurate. 
</P>
