<HEADLINE>
<P>
EARNINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Viacom Inc.: The New York-based entertainment concern posted a net loss of 
$34.7 million for the second quarter, compared to a $44.7-million loss a year 
ago. A non-cash charge of $32.8 million related to incentive compensation 
contributed to the loss, the company said. Viacom reported second-quarter 
revenue of $364 million, 22% higher than in the 1988 period; syndication of 
"The Cosby Show" and increased advertising and affiliate income from MTV were 
cited. 
</P>
