<TEXT>
<P>
Transamerica Corp.: The San Francisco-based insurance, real estate and 
financial services company said second-quarter net income rose 13% to $91.3 
million. The company noted strong performances in its life insurance, consumer 
lending and leasing operations and said that capital gains from sales of 
securities totaled $10.7 million in the 1989 second quarter, compared to $1.9 
million a year ago. Revenue rose 6% to $1.7 billion. 
</P>
