<TEXT>
<P>
Eastman Kodak Co.: The Rochester, N.Y.-based photographic equipment and 
chemicals firm posted second-quarter net income of $60 million, down 85% from 
the record $390 million of a year ago, due to restructuring costs. Without 
those costs, the firm said earnings would have amounted to $287 million, down 
26%. Profit was further depressed by higher costs, including greater interest 
expense, and the unfavorable impact of exchange rate changes. Sales totaled 
$4.5 billion, up 9%. 
</P>
