<P>
SEOUL 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The death toll among passengers and crew from the Korean Air DC-10 that crashed 
in Libya last Thursday rose to 73 overnight when a young girl died of her 
injuries in a Libyan hospital, airline officials said Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
They said Bae Yoon A, 7, was flying to visit her father, a Samsung Construction 
Co. official based in Tripoli, when the plane crashed on landing. Airline 
