P. M. BRIEFING; 
</P>
<P>
GTE WINS $100-MILLION LIBEL SUIT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
CLEARWATER, Fla. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A jury awarded $100 million in libel damages today to GTE Corp. after rejecting 
Home Shopping Network's claim that the communications company was to blame for 
lost sales. 
</P>
<P>
HSN contended that GTE did not give it adequate equipment to handle a large 
volume of calls in 1986 and 1987 as the network expanded into 11 new markets. 
GTE won the case on its counterclaim. 
</P>
<P>
The six-member jury reached its verdict after about five hours of deliberations 
in the complicated case following a six-week trial before Pinellas Circuit 
Judge Howard Rives. 
</P>
</TEXT>
