THE SIDELINES; 
</P>
<P>
FULLERTON GETS MURPHY 3 MORE YEARS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
FULLERTON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Gene Murphy has signed a three-year contract extension to continue as Cal State 
Fullerton's head football coach through the 1992 season, the school announced 
today. 
</P>
<P>
Murphy, 49, is about to begin his 10th season with the Titans, who have 
finished first or second in the Big West Conference in five of the last six 
seasons. He signed a five-year contract after the 1984 season, when Fullerton 
was credited with an unbeaten season after Nevada-Las Vegas was forced to 
forfeit the only loss on the Titans' 11-1 on-the-field record. 
</P>
<P>
Murphy's nine-season record at Fullerton is 48-56 (50-54, including two 
opponent forfeits), even though the Titans played 70 of those 104 games on the 
road. Murphy had previously been 15-7 in two seasons at North Dakota. 
</P>
</TEXT>
